In re Herbert Roy HARVEY, an Incompetent, by Daisy Harvey, His Guardian. No. 1805. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Nov. 28, 1938. A. L. Brook, of Muskogee, Old., for appellant. Cleon A. Summers, U. S. Atty., of Muskogee, Old., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed at appellant’s costs, for failure to prosecute, oh motion of appellee. '
